cast_shell: fullscreen the platform window on CastWindowManagerAura init

Without state-setting before the initial commit, ozone-wayland sends
xdg_toplevel.commit() with no state and weston-desktop-shell picks
configure(0, 0, array[0]), i.e. "client may choose any size". Chromium's
ozone default with no other input is to commit a 0x0 buffer; the kiosk
viewport stays 0x0 and weston-desktop-shell's background shows through.

set_maximized would also work and was the prior shape of this patch, but
under weston-desktop-shell maximize leaves the panel visible at the top
of the output: the toplevel is configured to (800, 448) and the kiosk
ends up 32 px short of the panel. set_fullscreen instead unmaps the
panel for as long as the kiosk holds the fullscreen state, so the
toplevel is configured to the full output bounds (800, 480) and the
kiosk owns the entire panel. Behaviour is identical under kiosk-shell
where every xdg_toplevel is fullscreen anyway, and identical under
fullscreen-shell where the protocol is the same.

display::kInvalidDisplayId leaves the choice of output to the
compositor; on this device there's only one wl_output so it's
unambiguous. The kInvalidDisplayId constant is reached via
ui/display/display.h, which cast_window_manager_aura.cc already
includes.

Pairs with patch 0005 (which sizes the WebContents child aura window to
the primary display) - 0006 fixes the OUTER wl_surface size, 0005 fixes
the child window's bounds inside it.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [kiosk-specific use case]

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>

--- a/chromecast/graphics/cast_window_manager_aura.cc
+++ b/chromecast/graphics/cast_window_manager_aura.cc
@@ -27,6 +27,7 @@
 #include "ui/display/display_transform.h"
 #include "ui/display/screen.h"
 #include "ui/ozone/public/ozone_platform.h"
+#include "ui/platform_window/platform_window.h"
 #include "ui/platform_window/platform_window_init_properties.h"
 #include "ui/touch_selection/touch_selection_menu_runner.h"
 #include "ui/wm/core/default_screen_position_client.h"
@@ -192,6 +193,19 @@
   window_tree_host_ = std::make_unique<CastWindowTreeHostAura>(
       enable_input_, std::move(properties));
   window_tree_host_->InitHost();
+
+  // bridgething patch: fullscreen the platform window on init so the
+  // wayland xdg_toplevel requests the full output area before the
+  // initial commit. Without any state set, ozone-wayland commits with
+  // no state and weston-desktop-shell configures the toplevel to
+  // (0, 0) (client may choose any size); chromium then paints a 0x0
+  // buffer and the compositor background shows through. Fullscreen
+  // also unmaps the desktop-shell panel so the kiosk gets the entire
+  // output rather than the maximized 800x448 inset.
+  if (window_tree_host_->platform_window()) {
+    window_tree_host_->platform_window()->SetFullscreen(
+        true, display::kInvalidDisplayId);
+  }
   aura::Window* root_window = window_tree_host_->window();
   root_window->SetLayoutManager(
       std::make_unique<CastLayoutManager>(this, root_window));
